WEBVTT

00:47.089 --> 00:50.049
NARRATOR:
On Christmas Eve, many years ago...

00:50.217 --> 00:52.635
...I lay quietly in my bed.

00:52.845 --> 00:55.138
I did not rustle the sheets.

00:55.347 --> 00:58.641
I breathed slowly and silently.

00:58.809 --> 01:04.480
I was listening for a sound
I was afraid I'd never hear.

01:04.857 --> 01:09.986
The ringing bells of Santa's sleigh.

01:28.630 --> 01:29.964
[SIZZLES]

01:30.132 --> 01:31.758
[GASPS]

01:43.812 --> 01:46.022
[JINGLING]

01:50.944 --> 01:53.821
[CLANGING]

02:27.231 --> 02:29.482
[JINGLING]

02:37.991 --> 02:40.076
DAD:
All right. All right, Sarah...

02:40.244 --> 02:41.577
...you had your water.

02:41.745 --> 02:43.830
Now let's get you upstairs
and into bed.

02:43.997 --> 02:46.582
SARAH:
But... But... But, I have to...

02:49.253 --> 02:52.088
He said Santa would have to
fly faster than the speed of light...

02:52.256 --> 02:56.092
...to get to every house in one night.
And to hold everyone's presents...

02:56.260 --> 02:58.928
...his sled would be bigger
than an ocean liner.

02:59.096 --> 03:03.099
DAD: Your brother said that? He was just
kidding you. He knows there's a Santa.

03:03.267 --> 03:06.936
SARAH: He said he wasn't sure.
He wasn't sure if Santa was for real.

03:07.104 --> 03:10.189
DAD: Of course Santa's for real.
He's as real as Christmas itself.

03:10.357 --> 03:11.691
MOM:
But he won't come...

03:11.859 --> 03:13.985
...until you're sound asleep,
young lady.

03:14.987 --> 03:16.779
Sweet dreams.

03:17.698 --> 03:19.949
DAD:
Santa will be here before you know it.

03:20.117 --> 03:21.868
So go to sleep.

03:22.744 --> 03:24.078
[JINGLING]

03:49.479 --> 03:52.231
[HUFFS]

03:56.069 --> 03:58.154
Mm-hm.

04:06.830 --> 04:09.040
"Stark, barren.

04:12.252 --> 04:14.754
Devoid of life."

04:15.505 --> 04:16.880
[FOOTSTEPS]

04:25.682 --> 04:27.934
DAD:
He's gotta be asleep by now.

04:28.101 --> 04:29.810
MOM:
He used to stay awake all night...

04:29.978 --> 04:32.146
...waiting for Santa.

04:32.564 --> 04:35.858
DAD:
Think those days are just about over.

04:36.068 --> 04:37.985
MOM:
That would be sad if that were true.

04:38.153 --> 04:41.656
DAD:
Yeah, an end of the magic.

04:43.075 --> 04:45.368
MOM:
Merry Christmas, sweetheart.

04:52.876 --> 04:54.627
DAD:
See, he's out like a light.

04:54.795 --> 04:57.964
An express train
wouldn't wake him up now.

05:01.218 --> 05:03.386
[THINKING]
"End of the magic"?

05:10.227 --> 05:11.852
[TICKING]

05:30.205 --> 05:31.706
[TICKING STOPS]

05:45.429 --> 05:50.016
[RUMBLING]

06:06.450 --> 06:07.783
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

06:15.417 --> 06:17.460
[CHUGGING]

06:19.421 --> 06:22.298
[BRAKES SQUEALING]

06:59.711 --> 07:02.505
[TRAIN CREAKING]

07:15.227 --> 07:19.021
CONDUCTOR:
All aboard!

07:22.275 --> 07:26.237
All aboard!

07:53.890 --> 07:56.559
Well? You coming?

07:57.894 --> 07:59.061
Where?

07:59.271 --> 08:01.397
Why, to the North Pole, of course.

08:01.565 --> 08:05.401
This is the Polar Express.

08:06.403 --> 08:08.070
The North Pole?

08:09.573 --> 08:11.240
I see.

08:11.408 --> 08:12.741
Hold this, please.

08:12.909 --> 08:14.910
Thank you.

08:15.579 --> 08:17.538
Is this you?

08:19.332 --> 08:21.167
- Yeah.
- Well, it says here...

08:21.334 --> 08:26.005
...no photo with a department-store
Santa this year, no letter to Santa.

08:26.173 --> 08:29.842
And you made your sister
put out the milk and cookies. Mm-mm.

08:30.427 --> 08:32.678
Sounds to me like
this is your crucial year.

08:32.846 --> 08:37.224
If I were you, I would think
about climbing onboard.

08:40.020 --> 08:44.440
Come on, come on, come on.
I've got a schedule to keep... Oh.

08:47.194 --> 08:49.528
Suit yourself.

08:53.033 --> 08:55.743
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

09:35.158 --> 09:36.951
[CONDUCTOR CLEARS THROAT]

09:49.881 --> 09:51.507
KIDS [SINGING]:
'Cause that's the way things happen

09:51.675 --> 09:53.509
On the Polar Express

09:53.677 --> 09:56.679
whoo, whoo, the whistle blows
That's the sound of her singing

09:56.888 --> 10:00.140
Ding, ding, the bell will ring
Golly, look at her go

10:00.308 --> 10:03.686
You wonder if we'll get there soon
Anybody's guess

10:03.895 --> 10:07.147
'Cause that's the way things happen
On the Polar Express

10:07.315 --> 10:10.859
When we get there
We'll scream, "Yay!"

10:11.027 --> 10:13.320
We'll arrive with
A bang, bang, bang

10:13.488 --> 10:15.698
Boom, boom, boom
Laughing all the way

10:15.907 --> 10:19.034
With a comfy seat and lots to eat
Boy, it's just the best

10:19.202 --> 10:22.454
Wish it wouldn't ever have to end

10:22.622 --> 10:25.374
