18:28.441 --> 18:31.109
Hey, what are you doing?
You're gonna get us all in trouble!

19:24.413 --> 19:27.082
[WOLF HOWLING]

20:24.307 --> 20:26.474
[BIRD SPITS]

21:02.345 --> 21:05.180
CONDUCTOR:
Young lady, forgive me.

21:05.348 --> 21:08.934
I believe I have neglected
to punch your ticket.

21:09.101 --> 21:10.936
May I?

21:12.855 --> 21:15.857
I left my ticket right here on the seat.

21:16.484 --> 21:18.360
- But it's gone.
- You mean...

21:18.861 --> 21:20.820
...you have lost your ticket.

21:20.988 --> 21:22.864
She didn't lose her ticket.

21:24.033 --> 21:25.867
I did.

21:26.494 --> 21:29.537
I was trying to return it to you.

21:29.705 --> 21:32.582
But the wind blew it out of my hand.

21:32.833 --> 21:34.334
[SIGHS]

21:36.212 --> 21:37.462
You can have my ticket.

21:37.797 --> 21:39.547
[CONDUCTOR YELLS]

21:39.715 --> 21:45.720
These tickets are not transferable.

21:46.514 --> 21:47.722
Young lady...

21:47.890 --> 21:51.017
...you will just have to
come along with me.

22:00.736 --> 22:04.489
You know what's gonna happen now?
He's gonna throw her off the train.

22:04.657 --> 22:07.575
Yeah, he's gonna probably throw her
right off the rear platform.

22:07.743 --> 22:11.329
Standard procedure. That way,
she won't get sucked under the wheels.

22:11.497 --> 22:14.749
They may slow the train down,
but they're never gonna stop it.

22:14.917 --> 22:16.084
Stop it?

22:16.252 --> 22:19.087
That's it! I have to stop the train again.

22:19.255 --> 22:21.548
KNOW-IT-ALL:
No, please, don't do that again.

22:53.039 --> 22:54.789
HERO BOY:
Where'd they go?

22:55.207 --> 22:56.875
What happened to them?

22:57.043 --> 22:59.961
Please, she's in big trouble.
You have to help me.

23:37.625 --> 23:39.292
Hey!

23:42.338 --> 23:44.172
Hey!

23:44.340 --> 23:48.093
I found your ticket! Wait!

23:50.513 --> 23:52.013
Hey!

23:53.265 --> 23:54.516
Wait!

23:54.725 --> 23:57.143
I have your ticket!

24:23.295 --> 24:28.675
[MAN SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

24:33.514 --> 24:35.390
Is there something I can do for you?

24:35.558 --> 24:37.559
I'm looking for a girl.

24:38.310 --> 24:39.561
A gi...?

24:39.770 --> 24:41.563
[LAUGHING]

24:45.234 --> 24:47.193
Ain't we all?

24:48.070 --> 24:49.863
I have her ticket.

24:50.030 --> 24:53.533
Well, lookie. Lookie here. What is this?

24:53.701 --> 24:58.246
This is an official, authentic,
genuine ticket to ride.

24:58.414 --> 25:01.916
Oh, you better keep this
in a safe place, young man.

25:02.084 --> 25:03.543
If I was you....

25:03.711 --> 25:06.379
I keep all my valuables right here.

25:06.547 --> 25:08.715
Right here in the old size 1 3.

25:08.883 --> 25:11.092
Experience shows
this is the safest place.

25:12.511 --> 25:14.596
Not that I have much use for those.

25:14.805 --> 25:16.055
Tickets.

25:16.223 --> 25:17.765
I ride for free.

25:17.933 --> 25:22.770
Oh, yeah, yeah. I hop aboard this rattler
any time I feels like it.

25:22.938 --> 25:25.023
I own this train. Oh, yeah.

25:25.191 --> 25:29.611
It's like I'm the king of this train.
Yeah. The king of the Pol Ex.

25:29.820 --> 25:35.909
In fact, I am the king
of the North Pole!

25:37.620 --> 25:39.954
Oh, where's my manners? Sit, sit. Sit.

25:40.122 --> 25:41.789
Take a load off.

25:41.957 --> 25:44.292
Hey, would you like some Joe?

25:44.460 --> 25:49.964
Nice hot refreshment.
Perfect for a cold winter's night.

25:57.640 --> 25:59.057
[COUGHING]

25:59.892 --> 26:01.893
There. Bless you.

26:03.646 --> 26:05.980
What about Santa?

26:06.148 --> 26:09.817
- Santa?
- Isn't he the king of the North Pole?

26:09.985 --> 26:13.238
You mean this guy? Huh?

26:13.864 --> 26:18.076
Ho-ho-ho, ho-ho-ho.

26:28.379 --> 26:33.007
What exactly is your persuasion
on the big man?

26:33.175 --> 26:34.509
Since you brought him up.

26:36.845 --> 26:38.846
Well, I....

26:39.014 --> 26:41.182
I want to believe.

26:42.017 --> 26:45.103
- But...
- But you don't wanna be bamboozled.

26:45.271 --> 26:48.356
You don't wanna be
led down the primrose path.

26:48.524 --> 26:52.694
You don't wanna be conned or duped,
have the wool pulled over your eyes.

26:52.903 --> 26:57.031
Hoodwinked. You don't wanna be
taken for a ride, railroaded.

27:00.869 --> 27:03.913
Seeing is believing.

27:04.415 --> 27:05.873
Am I right?

27:06.917 --> 27:09.377
But what about this train?

27:11.005 --> 27:12.380
What about it?

27:12.548 --> 27:15.550
We're all really going
to the North Pole...

27:15.718 --> 27:16.926
...aren't we?

27:17.219 --> 27:19.512
Aren't we?

27:20.472 --> 27:24.892
Are you saying
that this is all just a dream?

27:25.060 --> 27:28.688
You said it, kid. Not me.

27:31.066 --> 27:32.567
Ah.

27:32.735 --> 27:36.195
So let's go find that girl.

27:42.453 --> 27:44.579
One other thing.

27:45.831 --> 27:47.999
Do you believe in ghosts?

27:51.712 --> 27:53.588
Interesting.

27:56.258 --> 27:57.759
HERO BOY:
Wait.

28:00.179 --> 28:01.429
Wait!

28:08.270 --> 28:09.937
Wait!

28:14.902 --> 28:16.444
I have to wake up.

28:16.612 --> 28:18.696
Yeah. I have to wake up.

28:19.031 --> 28:22.283
Wake up. Wake up. Wake up.

28:22.534 --> 28:24.702
Wake up!

28:27.206 --> 28:31.459
Wake up, wake up.
Wake up, wake up!

28:36.090 --> 28:38.299
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

28:40.302 --> 28:43.763
HOBO:
Kid!

28:43.931 --> 28:46.140
Kid, get your head out of the clouds!

28:46.308 --> 28:47.809
Wake up, kid!

28:48.018 --> 28:51.813
There's no sleepwalking
on the Polar Express.

28:52.773 --> 28:54.649
We gotta jump them knuckles.

28:57.319 --> 28:59.320
Come on, kid. Flip my shoulders.

28:59.488 --> 29:01.322
Grab my lily.

29:01.782 --> 29:03.324
[GRUNTS]

29:03.951 --> 29:06.452
That skirt you're chasing
must have moved on ahead.

29:07.121 --> 29:11.040
- We gotta hightail it to the hog, pronto.
- To the hog?

29:11.834 --> 29:15.169
The engine. The engine, you tenderfoot.

29:15.337 --> 29:18.589
We gotta make the engine
before we hit Flat Top Tunnel.

29:18.757 --> 29:20.425
How come?

29:20.592 --> 29:23.177
So many questions.

29:23.637 --> 29:27.974
There is but one inch of clearance
between the roof of this rattler...

29:28.142 --> 29:31.018
...and the roof of Flat Top Tunnel.

29:31.186 --> 29:33.062
Savvy?

29:36.191 --> 29:39.193
It's just the run up to the hump, kid.

29:40.070 --> 29:41.696
This will be interesting.

29:55.961 --> 29:57.670
[GRUNTING]

30:04.887 --> 30:06.637
Get back on, kid. Hurry!

30:06.805 --> 30:09.098
Grab my muck stick.

30:09.975 --> 30:11.309
[SCREAMING]

30:44.760 --> 30:47.261
There's only one trick to this, kid.

30:48.430 --> 30:49.931
When I say "jump"...

30:52.392 --> 30:56.270
...you jump!

30:56.438 --> 30:58.356
Ah!

31:19.127 --> 31:22.296
You. I thought you got thrown off, and...

31:22.673 --> 31:25.466
- You're driving the train?
- They put me in charge.

31:25.676 --> 31:29.095
- The engineer had to check the light.
ENGINEER: - Here's the light. Careful.

31:29.263 --> 31:30.930
All right, now.

31:31.223 --> 31:33.933
- Oh!
- Oh! I got it.

31:34.142 --> 31:36.060
[SCREAMING]

31:37.271 --> 31:40.773
- How do you know how?
- It's easy. Come here, I'll show you.

31:40.941 --> 31:43.401
This big lever here, that's the throttle.

31:43.569 --> 31:45.653
This little one here, that's the brake.

31:45.821 --> 31:48.739
And those are the pressure gauges.

31:48.907 --> 31:51.492
And that rope is the whistle.

31:52.160 --> 31:54.495
- The whistle.
- Mm-hm.

31:54.663 --> 31:56.581
You wanna try it?

31:56.790 --> 31:59.250
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

31:59.418 --> 32:01.794
I've wanted to do that my whole life.

32:01.962 --> 32:03.462
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

32:03.630 --> 32:05.256
[SCREAMING]

32:05.841 --> 32:09.135
Hold still! Hold still! Don't move!

32:10.304 --> 32:11.345
Look!

32:14.016 --> 32:16.142
[SCREAMING]

32:23.525 --> 32:27.028
Stop the train! Stop the train!

32:28.030 --> 32:29.864
Stop the train!

32:32.868 --> 32:34.535
What?

32:34.745 --> 32:36.203
They want us to stop the train.

32:36.371 --> 32:37.705
[GASPS]

32:37.873 --> 32:40.041
- Which one is the brake?
- He told me this was.

32:40.208 --> 32:41.876
- Who?
- The engineer.

32:42.127 --> 32:46.714
- The engineer? This one looks like a brake.
- No, he said this was the brake.

32:46.882 --> 32:47.882
Are you sure?

32:48.258 --> 32:50.718
- Uh....
- Are you sure?

32:57.809 --> 33:00.519
ENGINEER:
Pull the brake!

33:00.729 --> 33:02.563
Stop the train!

33:07.736 --> 33:10.029
[SCREAMING]

33:19.915 --> 33:21.916
Caribou?

33:23.794 --> 33:26.045
- Ugh.
CONDUCTOR: - There's no Christmas...

33:26.213 --> 33:28.339
...without the Polar Express
arriving on time.

33:28.507 --> 33:31.759
Am I the only one who understands that?

33:31.927 --> 33:34.762
You. I should have known.

33:34.930 --> 33:38.766
Are you bound and determined that
this train never reaches the North Pole?

33:38.934 --> 33:40.559
But look.

33:41.812 --> 33:43.437
Caribou crossing?!

33:44.314 --> 33:48.067
I make that herd to be at least
1 00,000, maybe even a million.

33:48.235 --> 33:51.278
It's gonna be hours
before they clear this track.

33:51.446 --> 33:55.533
- A tough nut to crack.
- We are in some serious jelly.

33:55.701 --> 33:58.119
- And a jam.
- Tight spot.

33:58.328 --> 33:59.620
- Up a creek.
- Up a tree.

33:59.830 --> 34:04.834
- Lost in the grass.
- I'll tell you what's grass: our a... Ow!

34:06.962 --> 34:09.630
[CARIBOU WHINES]

34:14.469 --> 34:16.469
[SCREAMING]

34:18.306 --> 34:20.599
[WHINES]

34:24.478 --> 34:27.898
[SCREAMING]

34:31.277 --> 34:35.572
[WHINES]

34:45.458 --> 34:49.879
Problem solved. All ahead, slow.

34:52.090 --> 34:54.175
[GRUNTS]

35:35.842 --> 35:37.718
HERO BOY:
We're going pretty fast.

35:37.928 --> 35:40.805
Tell the engineer to slow down.

35:46.144 --> 35:47.728
HERO GIRL:
Slow it down.

35:49.648 --> 35:52.399
Watch the speed!

35:56.738 --> 36:00.491
Ah! Jumping jeepers,
the cotter pin sheared off.

36:00.659 --> 36:01.909
- What?
- The pin.

36:02.077 --> 36:04.245
- Where?
- There.

36:04.454 --> 36:05.996
- Oh, no.
- Oh, no.

36:07.040 --> 36:10.835
- They can't hear me.
- They can't? Oh....

36:13.255 --> 36:16.131
CONDUCTOR: I don't like the look of this.
Quick, under the safety bar.

36:18.218 --> 36:20.010
Is everything all right?
What should we do?

36:20.178 --> 36:24.098
Well, considering the fact that we have
lost communication with the engineer...

36:24.266 --> 36:27.893
...we are standing totally exposed
on the front of the locomotive...

36:28.061 --> 36:31.230
...the train appears to be
accelerating uncontrollably...

36:31.398 --> 36:35.234
...and we are rapidly
approaching Glacier Gulch...

36:35.402 --> 36:38.904
...which just happens to be the steepest
downhill grade in the world...

36:39.072 --> 36:42.366
...I suggest we all hold on...

36:42.909 --> 36:44.410
...tightly!

36:44.578 --> 36:46.120
[ALL SCREAMING]

37:05.307 --> 37:07.141
- The pin.
- The pin.

37:23.533 --> 37:25.492
[GRUNTING]

37:26.828 --> 37:30.581
Jiminy Christmas, the ice has frozen
over the tracks.

37:52.979 --> 37:55.147
Hold on. Hold on. No, no.

37:56.066 --> 37:58.192
Come on. Watch your step.

37:58.360 --> 38:01.570
Come on, sweetie.
Up you go. Up you go.

38:02.781 --> 38:06.492
- Shh.
- Put your feet on here. On here.

38:08.995 --> 38:10.329
CONDUCTOR:
Little adventure, huh?

38:10.497 --> 38:12.873
Young man, quick thinking on your part.

38:34.020 --> 38:36.730
Step to your left, please. To your left.

38:39.109 --> 38:40.401
Oh!

38:40.610 --> 38:44.113
Well, that is more like it.

38:46.491 --> 38:48.534
What in the name of Mike?

38:48.702 --> 38:50.035
[CRACKING]

38:52.330 --> 38:53.747
Look.

38:56.418 --> 38:59.169
Get us the blazes out of here!

39:07.429 --> 39:09.013
Turn this sled around.

39:27.449 --> 39:28.907
Look there.

39:31.619 --> 39:32.953
Tracks.

39:33.121 --> 39:34.538
Dead ahead.

39:40.378 --> 39:41.462
Right.

39:47.302 --> 39:48.302
Left.

39:53.808 --> 39:54.808
Right.

39:58.730 --> 39:59.980
Hang a Louie.

40:03.109 --> 40:04.485
Toss a Ritchie.

40:07.822 --> 40:09.490
Port astern.

40:11.701 --> 40:13.494
To the starboard.

40:14.829 --> 40:17.414
HERO BOY: - My slipper.
- You're gonna lose your ticket.

40:17.582 --> 40:19.458
It's not my ticket, it's yours.

40:19.626 --> 40:21.460
- It's my ticket?
- Yes.

40:21.628 --> 40:23.754
Right. Keep up with me. Left.

40:24.089 --> 40:26.507
Right. Left.

40:30.512 --> 40:31.845
Right.

40:32.222 --> 40:33.514
Left.

40:33.681 --> 40:35.015
Right.

40:35.225 --> 40:37.184
Left. Right.

40:40.855 --> 40:42.189
- Oh, no!
- Oh, no!

40:44.359 --> 40:46.235
Brace yourselves!

40:57.288 --> 40:59.206
Well, that's more like it.

41:01.543 --> 41:03.127
Thank you.

41:03.294 --> 41:06.547
Thank you. I can't believe
you found my ticket.

41:07.132 --> 41:09.758
Did someone say they found a ticket?

41:11.761 --> 41:15.180
Well, in that case.... Tickets, please.

41:20.478 --> 41:22.187
[COUGHS]

41:24.065 --> 41:25.566
Thank you.

41:27.318 --> 41:31.238
HERO GIRL: "L-E"?
-Hey, just like that know-it-all kid.

41:46.171 --> 41:47.504
CONDUCTOR:
Watch your step.

41:47.672 --> 41:50.924
Tricky walking up here. It's mighty slick.
Mighty slick, I tell you.

41:51.092 --> 41:55.012
Oh, whoop... There you go.
What did I tell you?

41:55.180 --> 42:00.267
Years ago, on my first Christmas Eve run,
I was up on the roof making my rounds...

42:00.435 --> 42:02.394
...when I slipped on the ice myself.

42:02.562 --> 42:05.939
I reached out for a hand iron,
but it broke off. I slid and fell.

42:06.107 --> 42:10.110
And yet, I did not fall off this train.

42:10.737 --> 42:12.946
Someone saved you?

42:13.114 --> 42:15.115
Or something.

42:18.036 --> 42:19.328
An angel.

42:20.246 --> 42:21.914
Maybe.

42:22.081 --> 42:24.124
Wait. Wait.

42:24.959 --> 42:28.128
What did he look like? Did you see him?

42:29.297 --> 42:33.133
No, sir. But sometimes
seeing is believing.

42:33.551 --> 42:38.639
And sometimes the most real things
in the world are the things we can't see.

42:43.937 --> 42:46.855
Ah, the forsaken and the abandoned.

42:47.982 --> 42:51.985
Mind your step, now.
These poor toys have suffered enough...

42:52.153 --> 42:56.490
...being left to rust and decay in the
back alleys and vacant lots of the world.

42:56.991 --> 42:58.825
What are they doing here?

42:58.993 --> 43:01.161
It's a new concept
the boss came up with.

43:01.371 --> 43:04.748
Instead of being thrown away,
they're collected. Refurbished.

43:05.458 --> 43:10.504
He calls it "rebicycling."
Something like that.

43:12.799 --> 43:15.175
HERO GIRL:
Makes me wanna cry...

43:15.385 --> 43:18.512
...seeing toys that were
treated this way.

43:19.347 --> 43:21.431
CONDUCTOR:
These hopelessly entangled...

43:21.599 --> 43:23.517
...string puppets and marionettes...

43:23.685 --> 43:28.021
...pose a particular problem. We found
the nimble fingers of our work force...

43:28.189 --> 43:32.526
...here at the North Pole are best
for working out those knots and tangles.

43:32.694 --> 43:35.195
Thank you. Uh-oh.
Double-locked here.

43:46.624 --> 43:50.043
You are just like me, my friend.

43:50.211 --> 43:52.629
- A scrooge!
- Ah!

43:52.797 --> 43:54.965
Ebenezer Scrooge.

43:55.133 --> 43:58.468
North Pole, Santa Claus, this train...

43:58.636 --> 44:02.556
...it's all a bunch of humbug.
A bout of indigestion.

44:02.724 --> 44:05.309
Oh, yeah. I know what you are.

44:05.476 --> 44:08.061
You're a doubter.

44:08.229 --> 44:10.814
A doubter. You don't believe!

44:10.982 --> 44:14.151
You're a doubter! You don't believe!

44:16.487 --> 44:18.655
[KIDS LAUGHING AND CHATTERING]

44:31.252 --> 44:34.171
Hey, you missed it.
We rode down some really sharp hills.

44:34.339 --> 44:36.006
We were on what looked like
a frozen lake.

44:36.174 --> 44:38.717
But I know it was just an optical illusion
caused by moonlight.

44:38.885 --> 44:41.762
He said the train was on ice.
But I said that's impossible...

44:41.971 --> 44:44.681
You can't put a train track...
Hey, where you going now?

44:46.267 --> 44:49.186
[INDISTINCT SINGING]

44:57.612 --> 44:59.029
Shh.

44:59.197 --> 45:02.115
LONELY BOY [SINGING]:
I'm wishing on a star

45:02.283 --> 45:05.452
And trying to believe

45:05.620 --> 45:08.789
That even though it's far

45:09.290 --> 45:11.792
He'll find me Christmas Eve

45:12.460 --> 45:15.587
I guess that Santa's busy

45:15.755 --> 45:18.757
'Cause he's never come around

45:19.258 --> 45:25.013
I think of him
when Christmas comes to town

45:25.807 --> 45:28.975
The best time of the year

45:29.143 --> 45:32.312
When everyone comes home

45:32.522 --> 45:35.649
with all this Christmas cheer

45:35.817 --> 45:39.403
It's hard to be alone

45:39.570 --> 45:45.617
Putting up the Christmas tree
with friends who come around

45:45.785 --> 45:52.165
It's so much fun
when Christmas comes to town

45:52.959 --> 45:59.047
Presents for the children
Wrapped in red and green

45:59.590 --> 46:05.345
All the things I've heard about
But never really seen

46:06.180 --> 46:08.682
No one will be sleeping

46:08.850 --> 46:11.977
On the night of Christmas Eve

46:12.145 --> 46:19.192
Hoping Santa's on his way

46:19.360 --> 46:22.487
When Santa's sleigh bells ring

46:22.655 --> 46:25.532
I listen all around

46:25.700 --> 46:28.869
The herald angels sing

46:29.078 --> 46:32.080
I never hear a sound

46:32.623 --> 46:36.042
And all the dreams of children

46:36.210 --> 46:39.045
Once lost will all be found

46:39.213 --> 46:45.135
That's all I want
when Christmas comes to town

46:47.513 --> 46:56.188
That's all I want
when Christmas comes to town

47:07.700 --> 47:09.159
Look.

47:11.829 --> 47:13.830
HERO BOY:
The northern lights.

47:16.667 --> 47:18.710
CONDUCTOR:
Hey. You three.

47:19.921 --> 47:21.713
We just crossed it.

47:21.881 --> 47:27.260
Latitude 66â—¦33'.
The Arctic Circle.

47:27.428 --> 47:30.764
And do you see?
Those lights in the distance.

47:31.724 --> 47:36.186
They look like the lights of a strange
ocean liner sailing on a frozen sea.

47:37.438 --> 47:39.439
There...

47:40.149 --> 47:42.192
...is the North Pole.

47:47.198 --> 47:50.033
KIDS: It's a magic carpet on a rail
It never takes a rest

47:50.201 --> 47:53.370
Flying through
The mountains and the snow

47:53.538 --> 47:56.456
You can ride for free and join the fun
If you just say yes

47:56.666 --> 47:59.960
'Cause that's the way things happen
On the Polar Express

48:00.169 --> 48:03.296
whoo, whoo, the whistle blows
That's the sound of her singing

48:03.464 --> 48:06.633
Ding, ding, the bell will ring
Golly, look at her go

48:06.801 --> 48:09.803
You wonder if you'll get there soon
Anybody's guess

48:09.971 --> 48:13.223
'Cause that's the way things happen
On the Polar Express

48:13.391 --> 48:16.476
When we get there
We'll scream, "Yay!"

48:16.686 --> 48:18.979
We'll arrive with
A bang, bang, bang

48:19.188 --> 48:22.190
Boom, boom, boom
Laughing all the way

48:27.196 --> 48:30.115
CONDUCTOR:
We made it. With five minutes to spare.

48:30.283 --> 48:31.658
We made it.

48:31.826 --> 48:33.451
[LAUGHING]

48:40.710 --> 48:43.128
[SOBS]

48:57.602 --> 48:59.853
HERO GIRL: There should be elves.
Where are the elves?

49:00.021 --> 49:01.688
KID:
Yeah, where are the elves?

49:01.856 --> 49:04.190
CONDUCTOR: They are gathering
in the center of the city.

49:04.358 --> 49:08.194
That is where Santa will give
the first gift of Christmas.

49:09.030 --> 49:11.531
Who gets the first gift of Christmas?

49:11.699 --> 49:15.535
He will choose one of you.

49:18.748 --> 49:21.541
- Look.
- Elves!

49:22.168 --> 49:24.753
[MARCHING FOOTSTEPS]

49:52.406 --> 49:54.741
CONDUCTOR: All right. All right,
ladies and gentlemen.

49:54.909 --> 49:57.661
Two columns, if you please.

49:57.828 --> 50:00.580
Shorter in the front, taller in the rear.

50:01.082 --> 50:04.751
Even-numbered birthdays on the right,
odd-numbered on the left.

50:04.919 --> 50:07.837
No pushing. No pushing.
But let's not dilly-dally.

50:08.005 --> 50:09.923
It's five minutes to midnight.

50:10.091 --> 50:13.677
Hey, what gives? It was five minutes
till midnight four minutes ago.

50:14.095 --> 50:16.596
Exactly. Columns of two.

50:16.806 --> 50:18.932
- One, two.
HERO GIRL: - Excuse me.

50:19.100 --> 50:21.559
- Question.
- What about him?

50:24.313 --> 50:27.023
No one is required to see Santa.

50:28.109 --> 50:31.361
Ladies and gentlemen,
you do not have to hold hands...

50:31.529 --> 50:34.948
- Come on.
- ...but please remain in your columns...

50:35.116 --> 50:37.534
...while we are in transit.

50:47.128 --> 50:50.630
- Look, you have to come with us.
- She's right.

50:52.591 --> 50:57.053
Christmas just doesn't work out
for me. Never has.

50:57.221 --> 50:59.806
But Christmas is such a wonderful,
beautiful time.

50:59.974 --> 51:03.643
It's a time for giving and being thankful,
for friends and family.

51:03.811 --> 51:08.606
People hang decorations and lights. Santa
leaves presents under our Christmas trees.

51:10.484 --> 51:12.277
Christmas just...

51:12.862 --> 51:14.738
...doesn't work out for me.

51:16.490 --> 51:20.243
Look, I don't know if Christmas
is gonna work out for you or not...

51:20.411 --> 51:23.496
...but this is Christmas Eve.
Don't stay here by yourself.

51:25.166 --> 51:26.750
HERO GIRL:
Yes, come with us.

51:27.293 --> 51:29.085
We'll go together.

51:32.673 --> 51:34.966
[CREAKING]

51:41.182 --> 51:42.807
HERO GIRL: Oh, no.
HERO BOY: Uh-oh.

51:50.858 --> 51:52.692
HERO BOY:
We're gonna be okay.

51:53.486 --> 51:54.861
[BUZZING]

51:55.029 --> 51:57.197
Maybe not!

51:59.033 --> 52:01.034
The emergency brake.

52:01.202 --> 52:03.161
The emergency brake.

52:06.874 --> 52:10.668
There's no brake. I can't find the brake!

52:17.176 --> 52:19.719
HOBO:
Take a break, kid.

52:19.929 --> 52:23.556
How about a nice, good hot cup of Joe?

52:50.042 --> 52:52.043
[SCREAMING]

52:52.211 --> 52:53.253
HERO GIRL:
We're gonna crash!

52:53.504 --> 52:56.673
[GRUNTING]

53:00.261 --> 53:02.220
We're spinning.

53:10.437 --> 53:12.897
["WINTER WONDERLAND" PLAYS
ON RECORD PLAYER]

53:26.495 --> 53:29.956
Shh. You hear that?

53:30.541 --> 53:31.791
The bell.

53:33.210 --> 53:35.587
HERO BOY: - What bell?
- The sleigh bell.

53:35.754 --> 53:38.131
- Sleigh bell?
- Don't you hear it?

53:39.508 --> 53:42.051
It's coming from that tunnel.

53:47.600 --> 53:49.726
That's the way we should go.

53:58.152 --> 53:59.736
Come on.

54:17.338 --> 54:19.839
Oh.

54:23.344 --> 54:25.637
[SONG SKIPPING AND REPEATING]

54:31.936 --> 54:33.519
What?

54:34.021 --> 54:36.439
- What?
- Come on.

54:41.528 --> 54:43.947
["SILVER BELLS" PLAYS
ON RECORD PLAYER]

54:48.661 --> 54:49.702
Come on.

54:59.505 --> 55:01.297
HERO BOY:
We're lost.

55:11.225 --> 55:12.684
HERO GIRL:
Yes.

55:13.894 --> 55:16.854
- Yes. I hear it.
LONELY BOY: - I hear it too.

55:17.022 --> 55:21.067
- I don't hear anything.
- Okay, it's down this way.

55:21.235 --> 55:22.485
Are you sure?

55:27.074 --> 55:28.282
Absolutely.

55:34.123 --> 55:36.624
- Why can't I hear anything?
- Shh.

55:39.211 --> 55:40.753
Get down and be quiet.

55:40.921 --> 55:42.922
[PHONE RINGING]

55:50.931 --> 55:55.101
ELF:
Yeah. Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

55:55.269 --> 55:56.853
Okay.

55:57.771 --> 55:59.897
Well, that was the wrapping hall, chief.

56:00.065 --> 56:02.608
- Just finished the last one.
ELF GENERAL: - How's it wrapped?

56:02.776 --> 56:06.738
ELF: It's wrapped in candy-striped red
with a number-seven holly-green bow.

56:06.905 --> 56:10.199
ELF GENERAL: A number-seven bow?
When we're this close to liftoff?

56:10.367 --> 56:13.786
What are they thinking down there?
Are they meshuggener?

56:13.954 --> 56:16.247
- What's the routing?
- Going to the States.

56:16.415 --> 56:17.957
Grand Rapids, Michigan.

56:18.208 --> 56:19.667
[GASPS]

56:19.877 --> 56:21.878
That's my town. I'm from Grand Rapids.

56:22.296 --> 56:25.423
[ALARM BUZZING]

56:27.468 --> 56:30.470
ELF GENERAL: We got a troublemaker
now. Just what we need.

56:30.679 --> 56:33.598
Things aren't bad enough.
What's his 20?

56:33.766 --> 56:37.060
Apparently, some kid
from Maplewood, New Jersey...

56:37.227 --> 56:39.645
...stuck some gum in his sister's hair.

56:40.230 --> 56:43.316
ELF GENERAL: New Jersey? Is that
the same kid that put the tack...

56:43.484 --> 56:45.610
...underneath his teacher's chair
last year?

56:45.778 --> 56:49.405
- No, sir. This kid's name is Steven.
- Steven.

56:49.907 --> 56:52.825
So, what do we do, chief?
Alert the big man?

56:52.993 --> 56:55.995
We talking nothing for Christmas here?

57:02.711 --> 57:04.253
STEVEN:
I didn't do it.

57:04.922 --> 57:06.672
I didn't do it.

57:06.840 --> 57:08.591
I didn't do it.

57:10.928 --> 57:13.346
ELF GENERAL: Look, it's....
It's almost Christmas, huh?

57:14.014 --> 57:15.848
We'll cut the kid a break.

57:16.016 --> 57:18.142
But put him on the check-twice list
for next year.

57:18.852 --> 57:21.020
All right, boys.

57:21.230 --> 57:24.315
Let's shut it down, all right.
That's it for this year. Come on.

57:24.483 --> 57:29.028
- Hey, boss, are we taking the pneumatic?
- Of course we're taking the pneumatic.

57:29.196 --> 57:32.365
It's the only way to get
to the square on time.

57:32.533 --> 57:35.785
- Let's go.
ELF GENERAL: - And time is money.

57:36.370 --> 57:39.163
Ready, and mount.

57:40.541 --> 57:43.251
Good. Close.

57:57.808 --> 57:59.642
HERO GIRL:
All right, get in.

58:01.061 --> 58:03.229
HERO BOY:
I don't know about this.

